1
00:01:51,185 --> 00:01:52,945
PATTIA CLUB

2
00:03:34,345 --> 00:03:36,185
<i>I do not believe that my dream</i>
<i>is just an illusion,</i>

3
00:03:37,425 --> 00:03:39,065
<i>that there is no karma in this world.</i>

4
00:03:39,825 --> 00:03:42,185
<i>If the ocean is meant to spill,</i>

5
00:03:42,265 --> 00:03:46,345
<i>let the water of misery fill my heart.</i>

6
00:03:46,425 --> 00:03:48,185
<i>If far away I must go,</i>

7
00:03:48,265 --> 00:03:50,185
<i>the storms I must weather.</i>

8
00:03:50,265 --> 00:03:52,025
<i>All for freedom.</i>

9
00:03:53,385 --> 00:03:54,425
<i>By Xu Meng.</i>

10
00:04:11,545 --> 00:04:12,905
What a shocker.

11
00:04:12,985 --> 00:04:15,425
All these smoke and mirrors
in superstition.

12
00:04:15,505 --> 00:04:18,944
In the end, it was all to run away
from debt collectors.

13
00:04:19,025 --> 00:04:21,785
We should be more rational.

14
00:04:24,825 --> 00:04:26,225
What's wrong?

15
00:04:26,305 --> 00:04:28,025
We solved the case. Why the long face?

16
00:04:29,585 --> 00:04:32,585
I'm wondering if this is the only answer.

17
00:04:32,665 --> 00:04:34,425
How many answers do you need?

18
00:04:34,505 --> 00:04:37,025
Even in a comic book,
they always say there's only one truth.

19
00:04:50,465 --> 00:04:52,665
What is going on? A grand reception?

20
00:04:55,985 --> 00:04:56,825
Captain.

21
00:04:56,905 --> 00:04:57,865
WEIYANG PUBLIC SECURITY BUREAU
NANSHAN BRANCH

22
00:04:57,945 --> 00:04:58,985
Let's go.

23
00:05:00,625 --> 00:05:01,665
Captain Feng.

24
00:05:03,025 --> 00:05:04,025
What's going on?

25
00:05:05,945 --> 00:05:09,265
You two solved a big case today.

26
00:05:11,305 --> 00:05:13,985
-We solved a case?
-How did you know we solved the case?

27
00:05:14,065 --> 00:05:15,705
I haven't even told you about it yet.

28
00:05:15,785 --> 00:05:18,945
Didn't you ask me
to ambush the pickpocket?

29
00:05:22,185 --> 00:05:24,065
He did see a briefcase

30
00:05:24,145 --> 00:05:26,825
with Qingsong Cement written on it.

31
00:05:26,905 --> 00:05:28,985
<i>It was hidden inside Wu Shanlong's house.</i>

32
00:05:29,625 --> 00:05:30,545
What was inside?

33
00:05:31,185 --> 00:05:33,545
Photocopies of the tender document
on Dongshan Mine.

34
00:05:33,625 --> 00:05:36,105
Does it mean the case is solved now?

35
00:05:36,185 --> 00:05:38,025
Wu Shanlong was the whistle-blower.

36
00:05:38,105 --> 00:05:41,305
Song Qingsong paid Director Li of the mine

37
00:05:41,385 --> 00:05:43,905
eight million yuan to win the bid.

38
00:05:43,985 --> 00:05:45,865
Director Li sure is cunning.

39
00:05:45,945 --> 00:05:47,025
He wants the best of both worlds.

40
00:05:47,105 --> 00:05:49,945
He sold the tender
to both Song Qingsong and Cripple Du.

41
00:05:50,025 --> 00:05:52,065
And in the end, they fought.

42
00:05:53,025 --> 00:05:55,785
I get it now. Director Li
conducted this whole farce.

43
00:05:55,865 --> 00:05:57,865
He said someone stole
the tender document from the mine.

44
00:05:57,945 --> 00:05:59,705
In reality, he was
just diverting attention.

45
00:05:59,785 --> 00:06:00,745
Exactly.

46
00:06:03,265 --> 00:06:05,865
Sir. We have good news too.

47
00:06:07,825 --> 00:06:09,705
Is it about
the missing father and daughter?

48
00:06:12,065 --> 00:06:14,185
They disappeared on purpose.
We have evidence.

49
00:06:16,385 --> 00:06:17,225
Good things come in pairs.

50
00:06:17,305 --> 00:06:19,385
When I see the chief next time,

51
00:06:19,465 --> 00:06:22,105
I'll put in a good word for you two.

52
00:06:22,185 --> 00:06:25,145
Sir. There's no rush for that.

53
00:06:25,745 --> 00:06:28,025
But my secondment ends tomorrow.

54
00:06:28,105 --> 00:06:29,465
I have to return to the police station.

55
00:06:29,545 --> 00:06:31,745
About my secondment evaluation report…

56
00:06:36,665 --> 00:06:38,585
Oh, He Yuanhang.

57
00:06:39,825 --> 00:06:40,825
You're crafty.

58
00:06:41,865 --> 00:06:44,985
Well, I have to bring something back
for that green-eyed colleague of mine.

59
00:06:45,065 --> 00:06:47,025
Before you return tomorrow,

60
00:06:47,105 --> 00:06:49,065
bring me the case summary report,

61
00:06:49,145 --> 00:06:51,545
and you'll have your evaluation report.

62
00:06:53,465 --> 00:06:55,385
Captain Feng, do I
have to write the report too?

63
00:06:55,985 --> 00:06:59,265
The quality of your report
will affect the quality of mine.

64
00:06:59,345 --> 00:07:00,425
What?

65
00:07:01,825 --> 00:07:02,665
All the best.

66
00:07:03,905 --> 00:07:05,625
But… Captain Feng.

67
00:07:05,705 --> 00:07:07,865
Tomorrow? I've stayed up late
for a few nights already.

68
00:07:13,785 --> 00:07:15,265
He. Go back and rest up.

69
00:07:15,345 --> 00:07:16,665
I'll write the report.

70
00:07:18,025 --> 00:07:19,265
It's okay.

71
00:07:19,345 --> 00:07:21,265
Working late is part and parcel
of being a criminal detective.

72
00:07:21,345 --> 00:07:22,705
You know what? Go back and sleep.

73
00:07:22,785 --> 00:07:24,185
Drop by my place tomorrow
at noon to check my report.

74
00:07:24,265 --> 00:07:26,345
You can also taste my wife's cooking.

75
00:07:26,425 --> 00:07:28,825
-She'll make noodles for you. See you.
-Okay.

76
00:07:29,945 --> 00:07:31,825
-Drive safely!
-Okay.

77
00:08:03,105 --> 00:08:05,665
Help yourself.

78
00:08:07,225 --> 00:08:08,065
Sir,

79
00:08:08,825 --> 00:08:10,905
I no longer eat coriander.

80
00:08:23,665 --> 00:08:24,745
Sir,

81
00:08:25,905 --> 00:08:27,745
you're now retired.

82
00:08:27,825 --> 00:08:29,505
Xiaohe has also grown up.

83
00:08:29,585 --> 00:08:31,985
Why don't you just enjoy your retirement?

84
00:08:34,625 --> 00:08:37,545
Are you telling me to give up?

85
00:08:39,465 --> 00:08:40,545
No.

86
00:08:41,144 --> 00:08:42,625
I'm telling you to accept
your current pace

87
00:08:42,705 --> 00:08:44,105
and you may continue to be useful.

88
00:08:44,185 --> 00:08:45,705
That's just giving up.

89
00:08:51,265 --> 00:08:53,065
Back then, you told me

90
00:08:53,945 --> 00:08:56,785
to let it go when it was time to do so
instead of dwelling on it.

91
00:08:56,865 --> 00:08:59,505
Otherwise, we would…

92
00:09:04,985 --> 00:09:05,825
Sir.

93
00:09:08,385 --> 00:09:10,145
Don't visit Yuanlongli anymore.

94
00:09:12,905 --> 00:09:14,385
I wanted to retire too back then.

95
00:09:15,105 --> 00:09:16,065
But you had to drag me in.

96
00:09:16,705 --> 00:09:18,465
Now, it's the other way round.

97
00:09:18,545 --> 00:09:19,985
Ran Fangxu.

98
00:09:20,065 --> 00:09:21,705
Just be frank with me.

99
00:09:21,785 --> 00:09:23,345
Are you going to pretend
for the rest of your life

100
00:09:23,425 --> 00:09:26,385
that the June 30th case never happened?

101
00:09:31,985 --> 00:09:33,505
I made a wrong call back then.

102
00:09:34,105 --> 00:09:35,065
That was on me.

103
00:09:35,865 --> 00:09:38,065
But it has been 18 years now.

104
00:09:38,145 --> 00:09:39,705
We've gone through every lead we had.

105
00:09:39,785 --> 00:09:41,185
There are no new leads.

106
00:09:41,265 --> 00:09:42,705
No new leads?

107
00:09:42,785 --> 00:09:43,985
Come here.

108
00:09:44,065 --> 00:09:45,905
-Sir.
-Come here.

109
00:09:46,545 --> 00:09:47,505
No new leads?

110
00:09:47,585 --> 00:09:48,985
No new leads? What is this?

111
00:09:49,825 --> 00:09:51,465
What is this?
What are these if not new leads?

112
00:09:51,545 --> 00:09:52,705
Sir!

113
00:09:54,545 --> 00:09:57,465
Why else do you think
I always visit Yuanlongli?

114
00:09:57,545 --> 00:10:00,265
Because I know
it has the most important lead.

115
00:10:00,345 --> 00:10:02,785
As long as Yuanlongli is still here,
the case can be solved.

116
00:10:02,865 --> 00:10:04,865
Let it go already, sir.

117
00:10:04,945 --> 00:10:07,265
No need to waste your life on one case.

118
00:10:07,345 --> 00:10:10,145
I can't! Just go away then.

119
00:10:10,225 --> 00:10:11,665
I'll just investigate it myself.

120
00:10:11,745 --> 00:10:12,585
Sir.

121
00:10:18,825 --> 00:10:19,665
Sir!

122
00:10:20,545 --> 00:10:22,745
YUANLONGLI INTERNATIONAL GARDEN

123
00:10:35,225 --> 00:10:36,585
MISSING PERSON

124
00:10:37,865 --> 00:10:40,865
Sir, what are you doing? Stop posting it.

125
00:10:41,945 --> 00:10:43,505
If you can insist on quitting,

126
00:10:43,585 --> 00:10:45,305
let me insist on investigating as well.

127
00:10:45,385 --> 00:10:46,625
We have nothing to do with each other.

128
00:10:49,945 --> 00:10:52,265
Your posters serve no purpose, sir.

129
00:10:53,625 --> 00:10:55,305
Just come back with me.

130
00:10:59,105 --> 00:11:00,265
Sir.

131
00:11:00,945 --> 00:11:01,785
Sir.

132
00:11:01,865 --> 00:11:04,305
Many things don't come with answers.

133
00:11:04,385 --> 00:11:05,665
I don't want answers.

134
00:11:05,745 --> 00:11:06,985
I want the truth.

135
00:11:07,065 --> 00:11:08,185
Let go. Let go of me.

136
00:11:08,265 --> 00:11:09,345
No!

137
00:11:09,425 --> 00:11:10,385
I won't unless you come back.

138
00:11:10,465 --> 00:11:11,665
I don't need you now. Let go.

139
00:11:11,745 --> 00:11:13,065
-No.
-Let…

140
00:11:18,665 --> 00:11:19,505
Who's there?

141
00:11:20,705 --> 00:11:22,825
Dad? What are you doing?

142
00:11:25,545 --> 00:11:26,385
Xiaohe.

143
00:11:32,705 --> 00:11:34,945
Xiaohe. Don't leave.

144
00:11:35,025 --> 00:11:37,025
Look. We're already here anyway.

145
00:11:37,105 --> 00:11:40,745
Maybe you, Uncle Ran, and I
can investigate this case together.

146
00:11:40,825 --> 00:11:42,745
I can't monitor you all the time.
I can't chain you to a post.

147
00:11:42,825 --> 00:11:43,985
I can't stop you.

148
00:11:44,065 --> 00:11:45,425
Whenever I go out,
you sneak into Yuanlongli.

149
00:11:45,505 --> 00:11:47,745
What if you fall sick again?

150
00:11:48,665 --> 00:11:50,585
Sick? Look at me.

151
00:11:50,665 --> 00:11:51,985
The very picture of health.

152
00:11:53,865 --> 00:11:57,905
Dad. I have work to do. Please

153
00:11:59,425 --> 00:12:01,145
go back with Uncle Ran.

154
00:12:01,865 --> 00:12:03,145
She's right.

155
00:12:03,225 --> 00:12:04,785
-Let's go, sir.
-Shut up.

156
00:12:05,705 --> 00:12:06,945
Xiaohe.

157
00:12:07,025 --> 00:12:08,825
You're here to find evidence

158
00:12:08,905 --> 00:12:11,305
to appeal against
Han Zi'ang's expulsion, aren't you?

159
00:12:11,385 --> 00:12:13,465
Since Uncle Ran and I are here,

160
00:12:13,545 --> 00:12:14,985
we can assist you.

161
00:12:15,065 --> 00:12:16,105
I don't need your help.

162
00:12:17,265 --> 00:12:19,545
Our investigation skills are exceptional.

163
00:12:19,625 --> 00:12:20,745
I don't need you.

164
00:12:20,825 --> 00:12:22,905
I can swear. I can swear

165
00:12:23,625 --> 00:12:26,425
that if we fail to find anything useful,

166
00:12:26,505 --> 00:12:27,625
we will leave right away.

167
00:12:27,705 --> 00:12:29,305
We won't disturb you when you work.

168
00:12:35,065 --> 00:12:37,025
What… What

169
00:12:37,865 --> 00:12:38,825
can you two do anyway?

170
00:12:39,945 --> 00:12:41,025
Right?

171
00:12:41,985 --> 00:12:43,585
I have no idea either.

172
00:12:43,665 --> 00:12:44,665
Don't play dumb.

173
00:12:48,465 --> 00:12:49,585
You know what?

174
00:12:49,665 --> 00:12:51,465
Take… Take the helmet for me.

175
00:12:53,425 --> 00:12:55,705
Stay here. Don't move. Come. Follow me.

176
00:12:57,025 --> 00:12:58,225
Where are you going?

177
00:12:58,305 --> 00:13:00,305
Just stay there. Don't move.

178
00:13:07,545 --> 00:13:08,705
MISSING PERSONS

179
00:13:12,785 --> 00:13:16,785
He Xiaohe. How can you believe
the words of a madman?

180
00:13:20,265 --> 00:13:22,265
-Run! Quick.
-What's going on?

181
00:13:22,345 --> 00:13:24,105
Quick! Quick!

182
00:13:24,185 --> 00:13:26,265
-It's dangerous. Move aside.
-Who's chasing after you?

183
00:13:26,345 --> 00:13:27,505
Careful.

184
00:13:27,585 --> 00:13:29,025
Dad! Who's pursuing you?

185
00:13:29,105 --> 00:13:30,425
-Careful.
-Dad!

186
00:13:39,505 --> 00:13:40,345
Dad!

187
00:13:47,865 --> 00:13:49,665
What are you trying to do?

188
00:13:49,745 --> 00:13:50,745
Who is pursuing you?

189
00:13:59,185 --> 00:14:02,585
Re-enactment is so effective.

190
00:14:02,665 --> 00:14:05,785
Dad. Can you stop messing around?

191
00:14:08,105 --> 00:14:09,905
This is called a re-enactment.

192
00:14:09,985 --> 00:14:12,585
It's Uncle Ran's expertise.

193
00:14:12,665 --> 00:14:14,145
Re-enactment?

194
00:14:15,505 --> 00:14:18,105
Put yourself in the shoes of Han Zi'ang

195
00:14:18,185 --> 00:14:20,065
and re-enact what he did.

196
00:14:20,145 --> 00:14:23,185
Then, find clues during the process.

197
00:14:23,265 --> 00:14:27,185
You're saying
that Han Zi'ang wasn't lying in ambush.

198
00:14:28,065 --> 00:14:29,345
Someone was pursuing him.

199
00:14:30,985 --> 00:14:33,745
That was why he hid in the cupboard.

200
00:14:36,065 --> 00:14:36,945
Where's your proof?

201
00:14:40,185 --> 00:14:42,545
Uncle Ran is back. He'll answer you.

202
00:14:43,185 --> 00:14:44,025
No need for that.

203
00:14:45,185 --> 00:14:48,065
Xiaohe is smart enough
to deduce it herself.

204
00:14:49,625 --> 00:14:50,985
Did you get it then?

205
00:15:39,225 --> 00:15:40,385
Help!

206
00:15:41,105 --> 00:15:43,905
Help! Help!

207
00:15:45,705 --> 00:15:47,185
Help!

208
00:15:49,985 --> 00:15:51,265
Help!

209
00:16:08,305 --> 00:16:09,305
I hear a ghost.

210
00:16:18,985 --> 00:16:19,905
Where is it?

211
00:16:20,505 --> 00:16:21,465
Over there.

212
00:16:36,305 --> 00:16:40,185
Han Zi'ang might have
been assaulted first.

213
00:16:40,265 --> 00:16:41,505
Then, he fled.

214
00:16:41,585 --> 00:16:42,705
Fearing assault,

215
00:16:42,785 --> 00:16:45,825
he acted out of self-defense
after he hid in the cupboard.

216
00:16:49,385 --> 00:16:50,265
Xiaohe.

217
00:16:51,265 --> 00:16:53,345
This is your logical deduction.

218
00:16:53,905 --> 00:16:57,025
You'll have to find the evidence yourself.

219
00:16:57,945 --> 00:16:59,585
Understood?

220
00:16:59,665 --> 00:17:01,025
You have to rely on yourself.

221
00:17:02,025 --> 00:17:05,385
Sir. You've seen how Xiaohe did just now.

222
00:17:05,464 --> 00:17:06,665
Yes.

223
00:17:07,625 --> 00:17:10,305
It exceeded my expectations.

224
00:17:10,385 --> 00:17:12,985
I know she is a capable officer,

225
00:17:13,865 --> 00:17:15,184
and I can't wait to see her
solve this case.

226
00:17:17,464 --> 00:17:20,065
Are you saying
that you still want to quit?

227
00:17:21,865 --> 00:17:22,704
Sir,

228
00:17:23,985 --> 00:17:26,385
I will wait for Xiaohe's
good news in Beijing.

229
00:17:27,665 --> 00:17:29,945
Then, I'll insert this case
into my teaching material.

230
00:17:31,105 --> 00:17:32,305
You're going back to Beijing?

231
00:17:32,985 --> 00:17:33,865
Yes.

232
00:17:50,705 --> 00:17:51,545
Dad.

233
00:17:52,625 --> 00:17:53,585
It'll be dawn soon.

234
00:17:54,945 --> 00:17:57,505
Uncle Ran has to catch the train.

235
00:18:14,865 --> 00:18:17,545
Let's go. I'll give you
a lift to the train station.

236
00:18:19,785 --> 00:18:20,665
Okay.

237
00:18:41,105 --> 00:18:42,785
AWARDED TO HE YUANHANG

238
00:18:42,865 --> 00:18:46,145
OUTSTANDING POLICE OFFICER
OF NANSHAN DISTRICT

239
00:18:48,425 --> 00:18:51,665
…THE STORMS I MUST WEATHER
ALL FOR FREEDOM. XU MENG

240
00:19:09,745 --> 00:19:13,145
YUANLONGLI JUNE 30TH CASE, SUMMARY REPORT

241
00:19:17,185 --> 00:19:19,185
<i>On August 24th, 1995,</i>

242
00:19:20,145 --> 00:19:22,465
<i>Xu Zhihong, father, and Xu Meng, daughter,</i>

243
00:19:22,545 --> 00:19:24,345
<i>were involved in an accident on Mount Wu.</i>

244
00:19:24,425 --> 00:19:26,785
<i>Xu Zhihong suffered severe injuries</i>

245
00:19:26,865 --> 00:19:27,705
-What's the matter?
-<i>and had to seek</i>

246
00:19:27,785 --> 00:19:28,945
<i>long-term medical treatment.</i>

247
00:19:29,465 --> 00:19:30,465
Dad!

248
00:19:31,025 --> 00:19:32,665
Dad! Dad!

249
00:19:33,265 --> 00:19:35,385
Save my dad. He fainted.

250
00:19:35,465 --> 00:19:37,465
Save my dad. Save my dad.

251
00:19:40,505 --> 00:19:43,305
<i>Xu Meng pawned her assets</i>
<i>and took out loans</i>

252
00:19:43,905 --> 00:19:45,305
<i>to pay for her father's medical bills.</i>

253
00:19:48,745 --> 00:19:53,025
IOU, XU MENG

254
00:20:01,065 --> 00:20:02,425
Didn't you say 8,000 yuan?

255
00:20:03,025 --> 00:20:04,065
How come there's only 6,000 yuan?

256
00:20:04,145 --> 00:20:06,385
You think I don't need
the handling fee? Huh?

257
00:20:08,305 --> 00:20:09,705
Don't just stand there.

258
00:20:11,225 --> 00:20:13,385
-Pay up now! Pay up!
-Pay up now!

259
00:20:13,465 --> 00:20:15,585
-Pay up!
-Pay up now! Pay up!

260
00:20:15,665 --> 00:20:17,265
-Pay up now!
-Pay up!

261
00:20:17,345 --> 00:20:18,345
-Pay up!
-Pay up!

262
00:20:18,425 --> 00:20:19,265
-Pay up now!
-Pay up!

263
00:20:19,345 --> 00:20:21,305
<i>As the Xus accumulated debts,</i>

264
00:20:21,385 --> 00:20:23,745
-<i>debt collectors visited them more often.</i>
-Pay up!

265
00:20:23,825 --> 00:20:24,825
<i>They shouted threats,</i>

266
00:20:25,425 --> 00:20:27,545
<i>pushing the victims into desperation.</i>

267
00:20:27,625 --> 00:20:28,945
-Pay up!
-Yes, pay up!

268
00:20:29,025 --> 00:20:30,625
-Pay up, Xu Meng!
-Xu Meng!

269
00:20:30,705 --> 00:20:33,145
-I know you're in there.
-Just come

270
00:20:34,625 --> 00:20:35,905
after me, you punks!

271
00:20:35,985 --> 00:20:37,545
Old cripple, come out now.

272
00:20:37,625 --> 00:20:39,905
-Get out now!
-Don't harass my daughter!

273
00:20:39,985 --> 00:20:41,145
-If you can stay in there,
-Stay put.

274
00:20:41,225 --> 00:20:43,025
-come out and pay up now.
-It's okay.

275
00:20:43,105 --> 00:20:44,225
-It's okay.
-Pay up!

276
00:20:44,305 --> 00:20:46,065
-Pay up!
-Bullying a girl now?

277
00:20:46,145 --> 00:20:48,025
-Come out now!
-Are you even men?

278
00:20:48,105 --> 00:20:49,025
<i>Our investigation</i>

279
00:20:49,625 --> 00:20:51,985
<i>indicates that Xu Meng</i>
<i>defrauded many people</i>

280
00:20:52,065 --> 00:20:54,305
<i>by repeatedly mortgaging her property.</i>

281
00:20:55,105 --> 00:20:57,265
<i>They had the motive to run away</i>

282
00:20:57,345 --> 00:21:00,785
<i>from their debt collectors and pursuers.</i>

283
00:21:06,105 --> 00:21:07,105
Mengmeng,

284
00:21:09,265 --> 00:21:10,625
death

285
00:21:12,305 --> 00:21:13,265
is

286
00:21:15,065 --> 00:21:17,505
our only solution.

287
00:21:22,505 --> 00:21:23,465
Dad,

288
00:21:24,865 --> 00:21:26,225
I don't want to die.

289
00:21:27,945 --> 00:21:29,345
Let's run away, okay?

290
00:21:30,625 --> 00:21:32,185
We'll disappear in Weiyang.

291
00:21:35,305 --> 00:21:36,545
<i>Vanishing in Weiyang</i>

292
00:21:37,225 --> 00:21:39,705
<i>became their only way out.</i>

293
00:21:44,825 --> 00:21:47,465
<i>According to the testimony</i>
<i>of Du Mandun, a Yuanlongli resident,</i>

294
00:21:48,145 --> 00:21:50,105
<i>Xu Meng visited the New York Block</i>

295
00:21:50,185 --> 00:21:53,665
<i>to devise her escape route</i>
<i>before she executed her plan.</i>

296
00:21:58,625 --> 00:22:01,185
<i>Elevators are operated</i>
<i>by the same generic key.</i>

297
00:22:01,265 --> 00:22:03,745
<i>Having worked in Dajianchang</i>
<i>for many years,</i>

298
00:22:04,345 --> 00:22:07,345
<i>Xu Zhihong was familiar</i>
<i>with tools and could make keys.</i>

299
00:22:08,665 --> 00:22:12,465
<i>Additionally, the Xus</i>
<i>also picked the date carefully.</i>

300
00:22:12,545 --> 00:22:13,745
<i>They opted for a day when the residents</i>

301
00:22:13,825 --> 00:22:16,265
<i>would be watching the reunification</i>
<i>of Hong Kong broadcast.</i>

302
00:22:16,345 --> 00:22:20,185
<i>The absence of people on the street</i>
<i>facilitated their escape plan.</i>

303
00:22:20,265 --> 00:22:23,065
<i>At around 4:30 p.m., June 30th,</i>

304
00:22:23,145 --> 00:22:24,625
<i>Xu Meng carried Xu Zhihong on her back</i>

305
00:22:24,705 --> 00:22:26,305
<i>and arrived at Yuanlongli.</i>

306
00:22:27,185 --> 00:22:29,105
<i>At 4:38 p.m.,</i>

307
00:22:29,185 --> 00:22:32,345
<i>Xu Meng and Xu Zhihong</i>
<i>took the elevator to the 18th floor.</i>

308
00:22:33,265 --> 00:22:35,025
<i>Before they exited the elevator,</i>

309
00:22:35,105 --> 00:22:37,465
<i>Xu Zhihong pressed all the buttons</i>
<i>in the elevator.</i>

310
00:22:49,985 --> 00:22:53,145
<i>After they left the elevator,</i>
<i>they split up.</i>

311
00:22:53,905 --> 00:22:56,865
<i>When the elevator stopped briefly</i>
<i>on the 17th floor,</i>

312
00:22:56,945 --> 00:22:59,745
<i>Xu Meng went to 1813</i>
<i>and hung the black cloak.</i>

313
00:23:00,625 --> 00:23:02,985
<i>Xu Zhihong then unlocked</i>
<i>the door to the elevator shaft.</i>

314
00:23:13,985 --> 00:23:15,505
<i>They worked together</i>

315
00:23:15,585 --> 00:23:17,465
<i>and dragged two wooden planks</i>
<i>with their footprints</i>

316
00:23:18,065 --> 00:23:19,665
<i>to the top of the elevator.</i>

317
00:23:26,065 --> 00:23:26,905
<i>Preliminary analysis shows</i>

318
00:23:26,985 --> 00:23:29,625
<i>that Xu Meng's and Xu Zhihong's</i>
<i>footprints, handprints</i>

319
00:23:29,705 --> 00:23:31,345
<i>collected on the elevator roof,</i>

320
00:23:31,425 --> 00:23:32,985
<i>and even the handwriting in the letter,</i>

321
00:23:33,065 --> 00:23:36,945
<i>match the ones collected</i>
<i>in their place of residence.</i>

322
00:23:37,945 --> 00:23:40,465
Dad. We must live on.

323
00:23:41,065 --> 00:23:41,985
Don't be scared.

324
00:24:00,905 --> 00:24:02,865
<i>When the elevator stopped</i>
<i>on the first floor,</i>

325
00:24:02,945 --> 00:24:05,665
<i>the Xus unlocked</i>
<i>the elevator door from the shaft</i>

326
00:24:05,745 --> 00:24:07,305
<i>and arrived at the lobby</i>
<i>on the second floor.</i>

327
00:24:32,665 --> 00:24:35,745
<i>They took the eastern staircase</i>
<i>and headed to B1.</i>

328
00:24:37,105 --> 00:24:39,185
<i>It is connected</i>
<i>to the underground car park.</i>

329
00:24:39,905 --> 00:24:41,785
<i>When Xu Meng worked in Pattia,</i>

330
00:24:41,865 --> 00:24:44,185
<i>she got her hands on the keys</i>
<i>to the underground car park.</i>

331
00:25:06,585 --> 00:25:10,185
YUANLONGLI UNDERGROUND PARKING LOT

332
00:25:38,745 --> 00:25:41,985
<i>They took the car park exit</i>
<i>and left Yuanlongli.</i>

333
00:25:42,545 --> 00:25:44,585
<i>That route was not covered</i>
<i>by security cameras.</i>

334
00:25:45,465 --> 00:25:49,025
<i>The Xus mystified their disappearance</i>

335
00:25:49,105 --> 00:25:51,225
<i>so that rumors would spread.</i>

336
00:25:51,305 --> 00:25:52,505
<i>The superstitious beliefs</i>

337
00:25:52,585 --> 00:25:55,145
<i>would also deter their debt collectors</i>
<i>from coming closer,</i>

338
00:25:55,225 --> 00:25:57,865
<i>thereby giving up on pursuing them.</i>

339
00:26:01,945 --> 00:26:05,225
<i>In conclusion,</i>
<i>this is a premeditated, voluntary</i>

340
00:26:05,305 --> 00:26:07,425
<i>missing person case motivated</i>
<i>by the desire to evade debt collection.</i>

341
00:26:16,385 --> 00:26:18,425
<i>Should any request to locate them be made,</i>

342
00:26:18,505 --> 00:26:20,545
<i>we recommend requesting the city council</i>

343
00:26:20,625 --> 00:26:22,745
<i>to enlarge the search scope.</i>

344
00:26:38,825 --> 00:26:40,745
WRITTEN BY, TIME

345
00:26:50,665 --> 00:26:52,665
<i>Written by Ran Fangxu,</i>

346
00:26:54,145 --> 00:26:55,145
<i>He Yuanhang.</i>

347
00:26:56,185 --> 00:26:57,985
WRITTEN BY: RAN FANGXU, HE YUANHANG
TIME: JULY 5TH, 1997

348
00:27:18,305 --> 00:27:19,305
Hi, Uncle Ran.

349
00:27:19,385 --> 00:27:21,305
-Hi, Xiaohe.
-You're here.

350
00:27:22,025 --> 00:27:22,985
Allow me to introduce him.

351
00:27:23,065 --> 00:27:25,305
Ran. R-A-N.

352
00:27:25,385 --> 00:27:26,585
Ran Fangxu.

353
00:27:26,665 --> 00:27:30,105
And this one is my wife,
Sun Yun. Director Sun.

354
00:27:30,185 --> 00:27:32,345
-Hi, Mrs. He.
-Hi, Ran.

355
00:27:33,305 --> 00:27:35,585
-This is for you.
-You didn't have to.

356
00:27:35,665 --> 00:27:38,345
Come in. Let me serve the noodles.

357
00:27:39,185 --> 00:27:40,145
Take the shoes.

358
00:27:41,585 --> 00:27:44,985
-Uncle Ran, your sandals.
-Thank you, Xiaohe. This is for you.

359
00:27:45,585 --> 00:27:47,105
What is that?

360
00:27:48,545 --> 00:27:49,825
Oh. A doll.

361
00:27:49,905 --> 00:27:51,505
Thank you, Uncle Ran.

362
00:27:54,465 --> 00:27:56,665
They both have something. Is this mine?

363
00:28:01,905 --> 00:28:04,585
A freebie when I bought
the gift for your wife.

364
00:28:05,505 --> 00:28:07,225
A freebie? I like it.

365
00:28:09,825 --> 00:28:10,665
It suits me.

366
00:28:11,345 --> 00:28:12,745
Come. Come.

367
00:28:18,985 --> 00:28:20,065
Here.

368
00:28:20,985 --> 00:28:21,825
Take a seat.

369
00:28:23,825 --> 00:28:25,785
Make sure you don't tell my wife later

370
00:28:25,865 --> 00:28:27,065
that I'm going back to the police station.

371
00:28:27,665 --> 00:28:29,065
But aren't you going back tomorrow?

372
00:28:29,905 --> 00:28:32,465
-You haven't told your wife?
-The noodles are ready.

373
00:28:34,025 --> 00:28:34,865
Come.

374
00:28:36,065 --> 00:28:37,345
How nice.

375
00:28:38,305 --> 00:28:41,825
Listen. My wife cooked
a whole table of food for you.

376
00:28:41,905 --> 00:28:42,785
Sorry for the hassle, Mrs. He.

377
00:28:42,865 --> 00:28:44,265
Not a hassle at all. Take a seat.

378
00:28:44,345 --> 00:28:45,305
Okay.

379
00:28:47,465 --> 00:28:48,665
It smells divine.

380
00:28:49,225 --> 00:28:52,745
Dad told me
Uncle Ran likes coriander best.

381
00:28:52,825 --> 00:28:54,825
I washed them all myself.

382
00:28:55,905 --> 00:28:57,225
Thank you, Xiaohe.

383
00:28:58,465 --> 00:28:59,745
Come. Let's have a toast.

384
00:28:59,825 --> 00:29:02,385
-Welcome to our humble abode, Ran.
-Thank you, Mrs. He.

385
00:29:02,465 --> 00:29:04,225
-You're welcome.
-Welcome.

386
00:29:08,345 --> 00:29:09,185
He Yuanhang.

387
00:29:09,985 --> 00:29:11,625
Are you hiding something from me?

388
00:29:14,665 --> 00:29:16,385
Why would I be hiding something from you?

389
00:29:17,465 --> 00:29:19,745
Didn't you say Ran was your apprentice?

390
00:29:19,825 --> 00:29:22,425
So isn't it a bit inappropriate for him
to call me Mrs. He?

391
00:29:24,825 --> 00:29:26,145
It sounds younger that way.

392
00:29:26,225 --> 00:29:28,105
Madam Sun sounds way older.

393
00:29:28,185 --> 00:29:31,145
Lie. Lie more.

394
00:29:31,865 --> 00:29:34,305
Ran is a top scorer from PPSUC.

395
00:29:34,385 --> 00:29:36,225
You're here for a secondment.

396
00:29:36,305 --> 00:29:38,225
There's no way he's your apprentice.

397
00:29:39,185 --> 00:29:40,425
Right, Ran?

398
00:29:46,025 --> 00:29:47,505
He

399
00:29:48,505 --> 00:29:49,705
is indeed my mentor.

400
00:29:53,225 --> 00:29:54,505
Did you hear that?

401
00:29:55,585 --> 00:29:57,825
Feng did this?

402
00:30:00,625 --> 00:30:02,345
-Eat more.
-Thank you, Mrs. He.

403
00:30:02,425 --> 00:30:05,665
You can hardly find a down-to-earth
young man nowadays.

404
00:30:06,265 --> 00:30:09,185
You're smart, capable,
and have the required qualification.

405
00:30:09,265 --> 00:30:12,225
I'm sure your workplace
will invest a lot in you.

406
00:30:13,345 --> 00:30:15,545
He will stay at the criminal department.

407
00:30:15,625 --> 00:30:19,105
Ran, you will support him, won't you?

408
00:30:21,945 --> 00:30:23,865
Actually, the criminal department
has a heavy workload.

409
00:30:23,945 --> 00:30:25,865
Even heavier than a bank.

410
00:30:25,945 --> 00:30:26,865
Xiaohe is still young.

411
00:30:26,945 --> 00:30:28,185
She needs her parents.

412
00:30:28,265 --> 00:30:29,905
Yes, Dad.

413
00:30:29,985 --> 00:30:31,385
I need my parents.

414
00:30:31,985 --> 00:30:32,825
For what?

415
00:30:35,465 --> 00:30:37,825
The biggest thing a father can do
for his children

416
00:30:37,905 --> 00:30:39,425
is to be a great role model,

417
00:30:39,505 --> 00:30:41,945
not to keep them company.

418
00:30:44,625 --> 00:30:45,825
Don't you agree, Ran?

419
00:30:47,905 --> 00:30:50,345
Yes. You're right.

420
00:30:50,425 --> 00:30:51,585
Oh, Ran.

421
00:30:52,305 --> 00:30:53,625
Are you single?

422
00:30:53,705 --> 00:30:55,865
I know many single women in my work.

423
00:30:55,945 --> 00:30:56,825
Do you want me to introduce
some of them to you?

424
00:30:56,905 --> 00:30:59,785
Uncle Ran doesn't need that.

425
00:30:59,865 --> 00:31:01,505
I know Ms. Qiao.

426
00:31:01,585 --> 00:31:03,185
She likes Uncle Ran.

427
00:31:03,265 --> 00:31:05,265
She's so pretty.

428
00:31:05,985 --> 00:31:08,385
Where does she work? She's quick.

429
00:31:09,305 --> 00:31:10,265
Mrs. He.

430
00:31:10,345 --> 00:31:12,145
I just arrived in Weiyang.

431
00:31:12,225 --> 00:31:13,265
I just want to focus on my work.

432
00:31:13,345 --> 00:31:15,505
I don't have time for anything else.

433
00:31:18,345 --> 00:31:19,905
Sir.

434
00:31:20,865 --> 00:31:23,025
How did the case report go?

435
00:31:23,625 --> 00:31:25,425
Oh. It's almost done.

436
00:31:25,505 --> 00:31:27,385
But I'm not so sure about certain details.

437
00:31:27,465 --> 00:31:28,985
Can you help me?

438
00:31:29,065 --> 00:31:31,745
-You can read it after the meal.
-It won't take long. Work comes first.

439
00:31:31,825 --> 00:31:32,985
Come. Take a look.

440
00:31:33,065 --> 00:31:34,945
We'll be back soon. Soon.

441
00:31:43,065 --> 00:31:44,865
Stop playing with it. Eat.

442
00:31:55,145 --> 00:31:58,225
SHE LEFT A LETTER. "I DO NOT BELIEVE
THAT MY DREAM IS JUST AN ILLUSION…"

443
00:32:03,705 --> 00:32:07,505
Where do you think they are right now?

444
00:32:11,385 --> 00:32:13,225
It's the first case of your life.

445
00:32:13,305 --> 00:32:16,465
Are you lamenting the fact
that you can't find them?

446
00:32:19,065 --> 00:32:22,465
No. Humans can adapt to many things.

447
00:32:23,065 --> 00:32:25,265
As long as they live a good life
where they are right now.

448
00:32:32,865 --> 00:32:35,265
It's good. Very thorough.

449
00:32:35,345 --> 00:32:37,745
I wouldn't have been able
to word it so vividly.

450
00:32:38,345 --> 00:32:40,785
Of course. I'm your mentor after all.

451
00:32:41,585 --> 00:32:43,425
Mr. He Yuanhang.

452
00:32:43,505 --> 00:32:45,545
Humility is often a virtue.

453
00:32:45,625 --> 00:32:47,225
Mr. Ran Fangxu.

454
00:32:47,305 --> 00:32:49,425
Humility in excess is arrogance.

455
00:32:54,425 --> 00:32:55,785
WRITTEN BY: RAN FANGXU, HE YUANHANG
TIME: JULY 5TH, 1997

456
00:33:01,225 --> 00:33:03,705
-What's wrong?
-The name sequence is wrong.

457
00:33:03,785 --> 00:33:05,225
No need for that.

458
00:33:05,305 --> 00:33:06,305
-He.
-It's fine.

459
00:33:06,385 --> 00:33:07,985
We must be truthful.

460
00:33:08,065 --> 00:33:10,345
I am being truthful. Listen.

461
00:33:10,425 --> 00:33:11,385
Investigation-wise,

462
00:33:11,465 --> 00:33:13,785
you are the main contributor
who solved this case.

463
00:33:13,865 --> 00:33:17,225
And in terms of your career,
you will stay in the criminal department.

464
00:33:17,305 --> 00:33:19,025
Whereas I will return
to the police station.

465
00:33:19,105 --> 00:33:20,625
-The sequence of our names
-Sir.

466
00:33:20,705 --> 00:33:21,705
-does not matter.
-Sir.

467
00:33:21,785 --> 00:33:23,545
Let me finish. It does not matter.

468
00:33:23,625 --> 00:33:25,905
Tomorrow, I'll take the evaluation
report Captain Feng gives me

469
00:33:25,985 --> 00:33:27,305
and return to the police station.

470
00:33:27,385 --> 00:33:31,025
I want to show Qu Dahai just how…

471
00:33:52,545 --> 00:33:55,105
-Why didn't you tell me?
-I tried.

472
00:33:55,185 --> 00:33:57,145
-What did you say?
-Sir.

473
00:34:09,985 --> 00:34:11,185
My wife is like this.

474
00:34:11,905 --> 00:34:13,545
She gets angry very fast,
but she also forgets about it very fast.

475
00:34:13,625 --> 00:34:14,985
She'll be fine in a few days.

476
00:34:16,225 --> 00:34:17,344
He.

477
00:34:18,625 --> 00:34:21,065
Have you ever considered staying?

478
00:34:23,505 --> 00:34:24,625
Of course I have.

479
00:34:25,225 --> 00:34:26,865
Why didn't you wait for me?

480
00:34:26,945 --> 00:34:28,905
I want to see Uncle Ran off too.

481
00:34:28,985 --> 00:34:31,665
Naughty girl! The floor is cold.
You came out without shoes.

482
00:34:31,744 --> 00:34:33,545
Wear your shoes. Come.

483
00:34:35,945 --> 00:34:37,264
You're here anyway.

484
00:34:37,344 --> 00:34:39,304
Why should I wear my shoes?

485
00:34:39,385 --> 00:34:41,545
Look at you. Your soles are dirty.

486
00:34:41,625 --> 00:34:43,465
When mom sees that, she'll scold you.

487
00:34:43,545 --> 00:34:44,865
Wash your feet when you go back.

488
00:34:44,945 --> 00:34:46,705
Okay. You have to teach me

489
00:34:46,784 --> 00:34:48,865
the 10th move of the evil-subduing
fist technique tonight.

490
00:34:48,945 --> 00:34:50,225
Of course.

491
00:34:51,824 --> 00:34:53,065
You see.

492
00:34:53,145 --> 00:34:55,824
I don't have a huge ambition.

493
00:34:55,905 --> 00:34:57,105
I understand.

494
00:34:57,185 --> 00:34:58,305
He.

495
00:35:01,065 --> 00:35:02,345
This isn't half bad either.

496
00:35:07,025 --> 00:35:08,345
Come. Let's see Uncle Ran off.

497
00:35:09,065 --> 00:35:11,505
Uncle Ran. Let me sing you a song.

498
00:35:11,585 --> 00:35:13,625
My class sings this song when someone

499
00:35:13,705 --> 00:35:15,425
-is transferring to another school.
-Sure.

500
00:35:16,265 --> 00:35:18,345
<i>Traveling the world</i>

501
00:35:18,425 --> 00:35:19,665
<i>The journey</i>

502
00:35:19,745 --> 00:35:20,745
<i>Is endless</i>

503
00:35:20,825 --> 00:35:22,545
<i>Lost and aimless</i>

504
00:35:22,625 --> 00:35:24,545
<i>One village after another</i>

505
00:35:24,625 --> 00:35:26,625
<i>Staring at the setting sun</i>

506
00:35:26,705 --> 00:35:27,665
<i>Sinking</i>

507
00:35:27,745 --> 00:35:28,745
<i>And rising again</i>

508
00:35:28,825 --> 00:35:29,745
<i>The world</i>

509
00:35:29,825 --> 00:35:30,745
<i>Remains unchanged</i>

510
00:35:30,825 --> 00:35:32,585
<i>The time remains long</i>

511
00:35:53,105 --> 00:35:55,265
You came all the way to Weiyang.

512
00:35:56,025 --> 00:35:59,145
And those old things in the bureau
won't even come to send you off.

513
00:35:59,225 --> 00:36:01,425
They are so heartless.

514
00:36:02,345 --> 00:36:04,425
Sir. They have work to do.

515
00:36:04,505 --> 00:36:06,105
They are in the special task force.

516
00:36:11,825 --> 00:36:13,745
WEIYANG STATION

517
00:36:13,825 --> 00:36:14,665
We're here.

518
00:36:19,265 --> 00:36:22,705
Xiaohe. Let me speak
to Uncle Ran privately.

519
00:36:41,025 --> 00:36:44,345
Have you ever considered staying?

520
00:36:47,025 --> 00:36:48,745
WEIYANG

521
00:36:52,225 --> 00:36:53,425
Maybe next time.

522
00:36:55,385 --> 00:36:56,265
I should go now.

523
00:37:04,985 --> 00:37:07,265
Xiaohe. I'm leaving now.

524
00:37:17,305 --> 00:37:18,825
She doesn't want you to leave either.

525
00:37:19,745 --> 00:37:21,025
But she's stubborn.

526
00:37:21,705 --> 00:37:22,985
She won't show it.

527
00:37:26,425 --> 00:37:27,345
Sir.

528
00:37:28,105 --> 00:37:29,025
Take care.

529
00:38:19,065 --> 00:38:20,785
Why did you leave so soon?

530
00:38:22,465 --> 00:38:24,705
You heartless creature.

531
00:38:24,785 --> 00:38:26,865
You won't even let me finish
what I want to say.

532
00:38:41,265 --> 00:38:44,665
Are you scolding the train or me? Sir.

533
00:39:01,465 --> 00:39:02,665
You decided to stay?

534
00:39:05,745 --> 00:39:06,585
Sir,

535
00:39:07,105 --> 00:39:08,545
you're right.

536
00:39:08,625 --> 00:39:09,945
I cannot run away from it forever.

537
00:39:10,585 --> 00:39:13,305
I'm staying to investigate
the June 30th case with you.

538
00:39:14,465 --> 00:39:16,585
You finally got it through
your thick head.

539
00:39:16,665 --> 00:39:19,145
I knew it. All these years in Beijing

540
00:39:19,225 --> 00:39:21,545
and you still care about this case. Right?

541
00:39:24,305 --> 00:39:26,425
Given your old age,

542
00:39:26,505 --> 00:39:28,345
without my assistance,

543
00:39:28,425 --> 00:39:30,225
you probably
won't be able to find anything.

544
00:39:31,065 --> 00:39:32,185
Good boy.

545
00:39:32,265 --> 00:39:33,945
You still care about me, after all.

546
00:39:35,065 --> 00:39:37,105
Xiaohe. Look.

547
00:39:37,185 --> 00:39:38,465
Guess who's back?

548
00:39:39,145 --> 00:39:41,745
Look. This is my apprentice.

549
00:39:41,825 --> 00:39:43,065
Ran Fangxu.

550
00:39:43,825 --> 00:39:47,225
When we work together, we are invincible.

551
00:39:47,865 --> 00:39:50,025
Peculiar cases or cold cases,

552
00:39:50,105 --> 00:39:51,505
they are nothing to us.

553
00:39:51,585 --> 00:39:55,065
Let alone a tiny Yuanlongli case. Right?

554
00:39:56,985 --> 00:39:57,825
He's my apprentice.

555
00:39:58,785 --> 00:39:59,625
My apprentice.

556
00:40:32,185 --> 00:40:33,305
Wait.

557
00:40:34,185 --> 00:40:36,345
I'm sure you've never left.

558
00:40:37,345 --> 00:40:40,105
When Mrs. Feng's grandson,
Ma Qiang's nephew,

559
00:40:40,185 --> 00:40:43,945
and Li Tieling's son
went missing in Yuanlongli,

560
00:40:44,025 --> 00:40:46,385
you helped me locate them.

561
00:40:47,945 --> 00:40:51,185
Sir. You got it wrong.

562
00:40:51,265 --> 00:40:52,825
I've been teaching in Beijing.

563
00:41:03,905 --> 00:41:05,025
This doesn't make sense.

564
00:41:06,265 --> 00:41:08,145
The train had already departed.

565
00:41:08,225 --> 00:41:10,625
You took the train and left
a long time ago.

566
00:41:10,705 --> 00:41:11,985
How did you return?

567
00:41:12,065 --> 00:41:14,185
How did the train return?

